HEADWORD: Gripper
<hw>Grip"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, grips or seizes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>In printing presses, the fingers or
nippers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gripple</ent>⟦br⟧
